Peggyâ€™s Cove is a relatively short drive from Halifax so we often include it in our shore excursions, incorporating other â€œattractionsâ€ along the way.Â  This may include anything from quaint fishing villages to the Swiss Air 111 Memorial site, located on St. Margaretâ€™s Bay.

As taken from NS Tourism<em>:</em>

<em>On September 2, 1998 Swissair Flight 111 crashed into the Atlantic Ocean southwest of Halifax Stanfield International Airport at the entrance to St. Margaretâ€™s Bay. All 229 people on board perished. The crash site was 8 km / 5 mi from the shore, not far from Peggyâ€™s Cove in the South Shore region. A short walking trail (30 m) to a monument in memory of the people who lost their lives can be found at the Swissair Memorial Site in Peggyâ€™s Cove in the South Shore region.</em>

