A full day of touring took us to the coast to visit Peggyâ€™s Cove, a Nova Scotia must-do for all visitors.Â  From there, we meandered along the Lighthouse Route and popped into the quaint community of Mahone Bay, known for its artisans, shopping and fabulous restaurants.Â  We ended the day with a visit to Lunenburg, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, stunning architecture and beautiful views of the coastline.

