Visiting the dramatic tidal changes in the Bay of Fundy is a must-do.Â  After experiencing low tide in Hallâ€™s Harbour, we made our way down the mountain offering superb views of the fertile fields in full swing with their produce.Â  At the bottom of the mountain is a rather gorgeous little museum, just off the beaten track, Prescott House.Â  The Georgian House with manicured gardens is definitely a place worth visitingâ€¦before heading back to Hallâ€™s Harbour to witness high-tide.

