Our first full day took us to the Annapolis Valley so we could explore the Bay of Fundy. Beginning in Hallâ€™s Harbour, we saw quite a dramatic seascape as the tide was out and the ocean floor exposed. Â We meandered our way down the mountain, through Port Williams and Wolfville to Grand Pre.Â  Here we learned about the sad history of the Acadian deportation and also visited the Deportation Cross, a memorial to the Acadians deported from here.

