Beginning in the Port City, we enjoyed a peaceful stroll around Halifax Public Gardens, which truly is a splendid sight at this time of year, full of colour and scents.Â  A short drive took us to Citadel Hill allowing for stunning views of the city and where we could witness the noon-gun salute.Â  Our guests also enjoyed some great meals in the downtown area and even managed to find copies of their immigration papers at Pier 21!

<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-497" src="http://bluediamondtours.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/IMG_0932-e1470828483892-225x300.jpg" alt="IMG_0932" width="225" height="300" /> <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-498" src="http://bluediamondtours.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/IMG_0944-e1470828514256-225x300.jpg" alt="IMG_0944" width="225" height="300" />

We had absolutely gorgeous weather to explore the Eastern Shore!Â  Beginning with a stroll on the Dartmouth Waterfront we then cruised along the shoreline to visit the Fishermanâ€™s Life Museum and took a step back in time at Memory Lane Village.

<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-499" src="http://bluediamondtours.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/IMG_0945-225x300.jpg" alt="IMG_0945" width="225" height="300" /> <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-500" src="http://bluediamondtours.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/IMG_0961-e1470828584291-225x300.jpg" alt="IMG_0961" width="225" height="300" />

An early morning departure from the city took us to Peggyâ€™s Cove, where we enjoyed breakfast on the rocks before meandering along the coastline to the quaint fishing village of Lunenburg.Â Â  Then to a very different fishing village on the other side of the Province, Hallâ€™s Harbour.Â  Here, we could witness the glory of the Bay of Fundy and the dramatic difference in the high and low tides.

